This paper deals with the mathematical modeling of coalitions and decision-making in games, which falls under the category of Game Theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves the study of boolean functions and codes, which are topics in Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Information Theory (cs.IT). The use of covering codes is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be classified under Combinatorics and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of upper bounds and the dimensionality of simple games, which could be considered a topic in Data Structures (cs.DS).
